inn1.comm: on the stumps, Ganguly leans forward to defend back to the bowler
It landed a foot outside off and slanted away. Umpire Billy Doctrove signals a wide.
Fullish, just outside off stump and Ganguly eases it in to the extra cover region for a single. Tendulkar now takes guard.
full-pitched, around the off stump, Tendulkar leans forward, opens the bat-face and steers to point
First four of the day. Full and on the middle, Tendulkar wrists it away past square-leg. It looks a pretty easy-paced wicket.
Broad gets his revenge with a delivery that teases the outside edge. Tendulkar was beaten on the forward defence
short of length, angling away from Ganguly who stands on his toes to punch it away to point
he gets it past point this time. Short again and a touch wide, Ganguly goes back and across and slaps it in front of square.
corrects the length, serves a fuller one, around the off stump and Ganguly guides it to point
back to short of length but bit more effort on this. It kicks up around the off stump, Ganguly gets on top of the bounce to push it away to the off side
beaten. Ganguly has a waft at a fullish delivery outside off and ends up driving inside the line.
straighter, on the middle and off, Ganguly gets right behind it, head over the ball to push it to the off side.

Nice line and length. Full, on a length, just around the off stump and it whooshed past the off stump. Tendulkar had it covered, though and shouldered arms. Now Tendulkar has some problem with the sightscreen. It is quite a short sightscreen. Just as well that Sunil Gavaskar is not playing. He would have ran all the way to the boundary.
Similar length, a tad wider but Tendulkar is uninterested and lets it fly past him.
Fuller, drifting on to the middle and leg, Tendulkar flicks it away to long leg.
on a length, around the off stump line, defended to cover
full and on the off stump line, Ganguly eases it to cover region. The pitch looks a beauty.
on the middle stump line, Ganguly wrists it to the on side.
beaten. Anderson gets one swinging away outside off stump and Tendulkar lunges at it, a touch late in getting forward, and the ball teases the outside edge.
And again. Lovely stuff from Anderson. Again on a good length, outside off and curving away, Tendulkar leans forward, shapes to chase it before withdrawing the bat at the last minute.
Ah! the perfect response. Fuller and on the off and middle line, Tendulkar leans forward to wrist it away past square leg.
Another one. Not so full this time, but drifting on to the middle and leg line, Tendulkar lets the ball arrive before flicking it away past square leg.
beaten. Lovely comeback from Anderson. This one lands on a length, just outside off stump and holds its line. Tendulkar pushes inside the line and is beaten by the straightening of the delivery.
on the middle and leg, worked away to long leg for a single. That was some over. Tendulkar was beaten thrice and in between, he put away two loose deliveries.
on a length, just outside off, pushed to the off side
The first bouncer of the day. It was outside off and Tendulkar swayed away from it.

137.1 kph, short-of-length delivery that reared up suddenly, chest-high, and Tendulkar is surprised at the extra bounce. He gets the bottom-hand off the handle even as he hops up and fends it away a touch ungainly.
on the middle and leg, worked behind square-leg for a single
full and just outside leg stump line, Ganguly tries to flick it away, makes contact with the top-half of the bat and the ball rolls to fine-leg region
138 kph, full and just outside off, Tendulkar lets it go past him. It was a pretty god over from Broad. He extracted bounce and had Tendulkar in a bit of a bother.
on the leg and middle, short of length, Ganguly tries to glance it away, doesn't connect and the ball runs off the pad
in the corridor outside off stump, Tendulkar leans forward and shoulders arms. That's the line that has troubled Tendulkar today.
fuller but  a tad wider to interest Tendulkar. He needs to get that line closer to the off stump
Again a touch wide and Tendulkar leaves that one alone. It is still a good line, wonder how long Tendulkar can resist the urge to drive
And again. Tendulkar's response is the same - lets the ball to go through to  Prior
closer to the off stump and Tendulkar lunges forward to defend. Another tight over comes to an end.
on the off stump line, Ganguly is quick to get on to the front foot and pushes it towards mid off
lands on the leg and middle, moves towards middle and off, Ganguly punches it towards mid off.

Hello? Ganguly decides to throw in his one-day trick. He comes down the track, even as he backs outside leg stump, but Broad is alert and hits the deck short of length. The ball whizzes above the flashing blade.
bouncer just down the leg side and Ganguly gets away from the line. Wide called.
short of length, outside off , Ganguly tries to punch on the up, doesn't connect well and the ball rolls to left of mid off and they will get a single
on the off stump line, Tendulkar goes back, gets behind the line and works it to square leg
short of length, on the off stump line, Ganguly pushes it to mid off and sets off for a run before he suddenly decides it is too risky. He sends Tendulkar back and all is well.
Ganguly backs away to the leg side, Anderson tries to follow him and Ganguly gets it up and over mid off.

Almost a mix-up. Ganguly pushes a length delivery to cover and sets off. Tendulkar is not interested, Anderson is and he charges towards to stop the ball. Ganguly turns back and just about manages to scramble home. btw Anderson's throw missed the stumps.
wide down the leg side
shuffles across, exposing the leg stump, dabs it away
bangs it in short  but again slipping down the leg side. Ganguly tries to pull but can't connect.
Almost gets his man with a yorker. Ganguly was pretty late in getting his bat down and the ball just about misses the off stump.
hits the short of length, around the off stump, Ganguly gets behind the line to dead-bat it away
full-pitched, on the off and middle, slants in towards middle, Tendulkar works it to right of mid on for a single

full and outside off, Ganguly drives down the ground and Pietersen chases it to push it back. He tries to flick the ball back as he dives but the ball makes contact with his leg and rolls back towards the rope. Pietersen throws in another dive but this time he makes contact with the rope (with the ball in his hands). It is referred upstairs and four is signalled.
full and outside off, sliced hard but straight to point
another one full and outside off stump, Ganguly carves it to point.
another full-pitched delivery and this time Ganguly drives but can't beat mid off
Overpitched on the leg and middle, Tendulkar whips it away in front of midwicket.
beaten. On a length, outside off stump and it held its line. Tendulkar lunged forward, a touch late in getting forward, and is beaten and ends up pushing inside the line.
length delivery outside off, guided to backward point
overpitched delivery outside off and Tendulkar drives but the bat-face shuts and the ball rolls straight to mid off. Tendulkar has not scored a run on the off side so far.
Ah! he has to make me look a fool, doesn't he? He leans forward to a length delivery and pushes to mid off for a single. Yes, Sachin, I will shut up!
lands short of length outside off and moves in towards middle and off, Tendulkar tries to whip it through the on side and gets a leading edge to mid off.
on a length, just outside off, Tendulkar leans forward to push it to the off side.
short of length, outside off stump and Tendulkar goes back and across to force it through the off side ring but can't beat backward point.
Fab shot. It was full and outside off stump, Tendulkar goes down on his back knee to drill it through cover point. The shot of the morning. See it in the Youtube.

Hello?! Tendulkar shuffles right across the stumps,  tries to work a short-of-length delivery to the on side and gets a leading edge to the off side. You will see this on Youtube only if some guy who doesn't like Tendulkar uploads it.
Wham! He charges down the track and slaps a short-of-length delivery on the off and middle through midwicket.
hits the good length region, on the off stump line, Ganguly is unsure whether to go forward or back and just pushes at it. The ball runs to the leg side off the inner-half of the bat
short of length, outside off stump, punched to point
good bouncer. It climbed up shoulder-high, Ganguly arches back at the last minute to dab it with soft hands and the ball runs down to thirdman
full and on the middle, sliding down, wristed away to long leg for a single
short of length, Ganguly shapes to pull but ends up mistiming it to wide mid on.
on the off stump line, full in length, steered to point.
Gentle seam-up stuff, loosener as they say, outside off and Tendulkar lets Prior come in to play.
50 arrives with a stunning strike. Tendulkar backs away to the leg side, as he charges down the track, and drives a length delivery inside-out over cover
And he does that strange shuffle again. He shuffles right across in a pre-determined way, and is beaten by a regular delivery in the corridor outside off stump.
beaten again. Tendulkar is bit late in trying to dab a length delivery outside off. It was almost as if he expected some other delivery and was getting ready for it.
tip and run. Ganguly pushes a length delivery towards mid off and they run with the stroke
beaten Full and outside off stump, Tendulkar is caught at the crease and has a lazy waft at it. Again, it was although he expected this one to be short. Hmm...
gets behind the length delivery this time and pushes to the off side. Another no-ball, though.
Charges down the track, backs to the legside and mistimes a delivery on the middle to extra cover
another pre-determined shuffle across the stumps, Flintoff hurls in a bouncer and Tendulkar pulls to fine leg.
full in length, on the middle and leg, Ganguly tries to work it to the on side, ends up slicing it uppishly to left of mid on
on the off stump line, Tendulkar leans forward to steer it to point

again that pre-determined shuffle right across the sticks, Flintoff sends in a fullish delivery hoping to trap him lbw, but Tendulkar manages to put bat to ball and pushes it to right of mid on for a single
On a length, around middle and off, defended with the full face of the bat
rund down the track, backs to the leg side in the process, Tremlett hits the deck short of length on the leg and middle line and Tendulkar guides it to third man
Slashed through vacant slip region. Ganguly decides to back to leg side and tries to slog a short-of-length delivery over mid on. Instead, it flies off the top edge high to left of Prior.
again he backs to leg side and drills a full-pitched delivery on the stumps to mid off
stays where he is and taps a length delivery close on the off side and rushes across for a quick single
That shuffle across to the off side and he places a short-of-length delivery on the stumps past the short fine-leg fielder in the circle.
full and outside off, Ganguly walks in to the shot, opens the bat-face at the last minute to guide it to third man
short of length, outside off stump, dabbed away to third man
Ganguly brings the third man in to play again with another dab. There was a wide slip in place. Ganguly got the ball to left of him.
And that pre-determined shuffle right across and almost gets trapped in front. He just about manages to get his bat in time and flicks it away to long leg.
tip and run. He leans forward to push to the off side, runs off the pad, Tendulkar calls him over for a quick single and he responds.
Full and on the off stump line, Tendulkar leans forward, opens the bat-face, lets the ball come to him before he runs it through the vacant slip region

fifty up for Tendulkar in quite a uncharacteristic fashion. It was full and on the off stump, not the length to back to the leg side but that's what Tendulkar does. He shuffles to the leg side and slices it through point. He has been constantly innovating today, manufacturing strokes in a pre-determined fashion.
on the off stump line, pushed to the off side
Ganguly breaks free with a slap over long on. He backed away to the leg side, Tremlett hurled it in short of length on the middle stump line and Ganguly flat-batted it over long on.
on the off stump line, guided to point
Full-pitched, outside leg stump line and Ganguly drills it straight down the ground. Four more. He is going after Tremlett.
Continues with his onslaught. Another slash and this one flies over the vacant slip region. Full and angling away from Ganguly who frees his arms. 100 up for India.
Tendulkar shapes to shuffle again, stops and steers a fullish delivery on the off stump to third man.
kicks up from short of length, Ganguly gets on his toes and gets on top of the bounce and places it on the off side
fuller and outside off, driven to right of mid off
hits the deck short of length, at the body, Tendulkar jabs at it and the ball flies off the gloves, down to the fine-leg region
charges down the track, Flintoff sends the ball wider outside off and Tendulkar drives straight to widish mid off
full, on the off stump line, pushed to extra cover. Two overs to go for Powerplay 3 to end.

Almost a mix-up. Yorker on the off stump line, dug out close on the off side, towards point. Ganguly sets off, Tendulkar also took a step or two before halting and Ganguly turns back to dive in to safety of the crease.
another yorker, on the off stump line, jabbed away to extra cover
Full-pitched, on the off stump line, Tendulkar drives powerfully but straight to mid off
bouncer, on the off stump line and Tendulkar sways away from it.
follows it with a yorker, Tendulkar shapes to flick and it runs off the pad to fine leg
Overpitched on the off stump line, Tendulkar stays adjacent to the line, no movement towards the line and drills it inside-out through cover.
Dropped by Tremlett at mid off. Tendulkar drives uppishly to mid off where Tremlett, 6''7', jumps, gets his palm to the ball but can't hold on.

Ganguly falls, going for the broke. He charges down the track , Flintoff hurls it short of length outside off and Ganguly slaps it over point. He doesn't connect well, the ball balloons over point  and Collingwood takes the catch running back from point.
bouncer on the off stump line, Tendulkar sways away from the line
fuller, on a length, outside off stump and Tendulkar shoulders arms
leans forward to defend a length delivery back down the track
fullish, on the legs, Yuvraj flicks powerfully to the right of deep square leg where Cook makes a tumbling stop
Full and on the legs again, Tendulkar wrists it uppishly but finds the gap perfectly. There was a long-leg and a deep square-leg and Tendulkar bisects the two perfectly.

almost edged to Prior. It landed on a length, around the off stump and held its line, Tendulkar was a touch late in moving forward and gets a edge with his forward poke. The ball fell just short of a diving Prior.
pushed to right of point and they rush across for a quick single
on the off and middle, pushed to cover point
full and slanted across Yuvraj who lets that one go through to Prior
gentle seam-up stuff, on the middle and off, defended on the front foot
Tendulkar continues to innovate. Another pre-determined shot. He paddles a length delivery outside off to fine-leg region.
fuller, on the middle but another paddle shot. Tendulkar plants his left leg across and laps it around the corner.
full and on the off stump line, Tendulkar drills it to mid off
Mascarenhas is unsettled. He sends this one wide outside off, wary of Tendulkar's paddle shots.
full and straighter, driven down the ground
on the middle and off, Yuvrak choses to stay back for some reason and pushes at it. He gets an inside-edge to square-leg
leans forward, opens the bat-face, guides a full-length delivery to third man
at the hips, tucked behind square-leg for a single
bangs this one short, on the off stump line and Tendulkar sways away.
fuller and Tendulkar moves quickly forward to drive but it rolls off straight to cover.
just outside off stump, Tendulkar waits for the ball to arrive, opens the bat-face and shapes to run it down to third man but can only get it to backward point
Tendulkar drives straight to him and will retain the strike. Ah! how many time have we seen this. Last ball and a single from the little master.
full and on the off stump line, driven to cover
takes a step or two down the track, backing to the leg side and drives inside-out over extra cover. He is toying with the bowling here.
short of length, on the stumps, whipped past square-leg for a single
jumps up from a length, Yuvraj jabs it away to the off side
It's Yuvraj's turn to retain the strike with a dab to third man
short of length, outside off, punched to sweeper cover

Wow! A stunning strike. Flashback to the best of Sachin. He charges down the track and flat-bats a length delivery right over long off. Up, up and over. Tendulkar has, now, scored 1000 runs against England.
on the middle, short of length, worked to midwicket
short of length, outside off, punched through extra cover for a single
short of length and outside off, Yuvraj has a flash and a miss
And he is beaten again. Too full to cut.
just outside off, run down to third man for a single
fuller, on the off stump line, driven to extra cover
beaten. In the corridor outside off, Yuvraj tries to cut it late but can't connect
full in length, outside off, Yuvraj tries to drive on the up and ends up mistiming it to mid off
gets a single with a drive past mid off
length delivery outside off stump, dabbed past backward point
full and on the off stump line, driven to mid on
too short and outside off, Tendulkar pulls it to deep midwicket
full-pitched outside off, driven to long off for a single.
on a length, around middle and leg, Yuvraj dabs it away to the off side.
gets this one to left of mid on for a single.
on the leg and middle, wristed past square-leg for a single
on the middle and leg, full in length, defended to the on side.
on a length, on the middle and leg, Yuvraj leans forward and punches it on the up past the diving midwicket fielder (Bell). Pure timing.
short of length, on the middle and leg, clubbed over midwicket. The boundaries are short here and he gets a boundary.
pings the extra cover boundary this time. Full in length and on the off stump line, Yuvraj drives crisply through extra cover
fuller and outside off, Yuvraj is beaten on the attempted cut shot
full in length, on the off stump line, Tendulkar tries to punch it through the off-side ring but ends up mistiming it back to Collingwood
beaten on that paddle shot. Short of length and it went over middle stump, Tendulkar tried to lap it around the corner but didn''t connect
on the off stump line, driven to cover.
fuller, straighter, on the middle and off, driven uppishly through mid off, down to long off
short of length and Yuvraj pulls it imperiously to the long leg boundary. The runs keep flowing.
on the off stump line, pushed to cover.
good tight line. It landed on a good length, around the off stump and Tendulkar just manages to defend to cover
fuller, on the off stump line and driven to long off
on the middle and off, Yuvraj shuffles across to glance it down to fine-leg region.
leans forward to dab a length delivery close on the off side, wants a single, but retreats after seeing Flintoff rush across. Wise decision.
full and on the middle and leg, Tendulkar retains the strike with a flick past square  leg
short of length, on the middle and off, punched to mid on
Full and swinging late, Tendulkar goes for a lofted stroke (mid-on is in), makes contact with the bottom-half of the bat and it balloons over mid-on and falls in no-man's land.
full in length and outside off, Tendulkar tried to carve it through cover point but doesn't connect.
slower one, ends up as a full toss, Tendulkar mistimes a drive to cover
Full and swinging, driven to sweeper cover. He moves to 99
on the off stump line, driven to long on for a single
short of length, on the off stump line, defended to the on side
short of length, on the hips, tucked to fine leg for a single.

Would you believe it? Tendulkar has gone for 99. Done in by a screamer of a bouncer. It kicked up from short of length and reared shoulder high. Tendulkar tried to fend it away, got his hands in front of his face and the ball seemed to have gone off his arm guard -- though no conclusive evidence was available from television replays --- down the leg side for Prior to take it. They let out a huge appeal and the fatal finger goes up. Tendulkar looks bemused. A wry grin, a shake of head and he walks back.  Did it brush the gloves?  The replays don't confirm or deny that.
leans forward to drive a length delivery to mid on
short of length, on the middle, worked to midwicket
gets off the mark with a glance to deep square leg
fullish, on the off stump line, Dravid is a touch early into his drive and the ball goes uppishly to mid off
leans forward to drive on the up to sweeper cover
short of length, on the middle and off, Yuvraj tries to whip it to on side and edges it on to the pad
short of length, on the off and middle, dabbed to third man.
leans forward to defend to cover
overpitched outside off and Yuvraj creams it through extra cover.
on the middle and leg, flicked past square leg for a single
short of length, outside off, swatted to the on side
on the middle and off, placed to right of cover for a single
slightly short of length, homing in on the off stump, Dravid stays adjacent to the line and cuts it late through vacant slip region
fullish, on the middle, driven to long on
length delivery on the off, pushed to cover
short of length, on the middle, pulls to midwicket
length delivery outside off, pushed to extra cover
200 up with a glance to backward square leg
length delivery, drifting down the leg side and glanced away for couple of runs
fullish, on the middle and leg, flicked past square leg
leans forward to drive on the up to long off
full and on the middle and leg, pushed to mid on
lands on a length, around the off stump, pushed to backward point
short of length, just outside off, slashed away to third man
kicks up from short of length, Dravid hops to get on top of the bounce and defends to the on side
on the middle and leg, tucked behind square leg for a single
fuller, on the off stump line, Dravid drives straight to mid off
bangs it in short, on the leg stump line, Dravid swivels to pull but doesn't quite connect well.
fuller, outside off, steered to backward point
fullish, on the off and middle, Dravid leans forward to flick it past midwicket
lands on a length, just outside off, Dravid goes back, taps it gently on the off side, looks for a run but Yuvraj sends him back.
gets a single with a flick-drive to deep midwicket
attempted yorker, full-pitched outside off stump, driven to left of long off
full and on the off stump line, steered straight to backward point
full-pitched on the off stump, driven to long off for a single
on the middle and off, on a length, pushed back down the track
full in length, angling away from Yuvraj who slashes it to deep point
full-pitched outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Yuvraj breaks free with a fierce pull. Short of length and pulled over midwicekt
short of length, just outside off, dabbed to midwicket
full and outside off, wafted away to sweeper cover
sliding down the leg side, Dravid can't connect with his pull shot
he comes down the track, tries to heave it over the bowler's head but mistimes the lofted shot to midwicket
overpitched on the middle and leg, driven to long on for a single
short of length, cut away to deep point
overpitched on the middle stump, driven to mid on
drifts down the leg side - the fine-leg is up in the circle and Dravid glances it past that man.
full and outside off, Dravid leans across to slice it past backward point for another boundary.
attempts a yorker, ends up just short of the blockhole and Dravid drives to right of long on
full and angling away from Yuvraj who slices it straight to point
on the leg stump line, flicked to left of deep square leg
gift-wraps a boundary. Fullish and on the legs - the boundaries are pretty small here and Dravid has no problem in flicking it away

Owais Shah, the substitute fielder, makes a super stop at deep backward point. It was slightly short in length, just outside off and Dravid cuts past backward point. Shah ran across from wide third man and threw in neat dive to make the stop
full and outside off stump, Dravid tries to reach it in an attempt to have a slash, gets an inside-edge to the on side
Yuvraj falls one short of fifty. Full and outside off, Yuvraj slices it uppishly  towards point and Collingwood dives to his left to pluck the catch inches off the ground..
bangs it in short, just outside off and Dhoni lets it fly past him
bouncer on the middle line, Dravid shapes to pull and edges it behind square-leg for a single.
short of length, outside off stump, Dhoni goes back and across to guide it past backward point
full in length, outside off, driven to cover
full in length, in the corridor outside off and Dravid is beaten, trying a cute dab to third man
climbs from short of length, outside off, cut to third man for a single
a rare full delivery to Dhoni - they have been hitting the short of length to him and driven to sweeper cover
lands on a length, around the off stump, punched to extra cover
short of length, on the off stump, tapped towards right of point for a single
full and wide outside off, Dravid chases it, slashing it to deep point
Dhoni gets in to the act. As expected it was a short-of-length delivery outside off and Dhoni hopped up and cut it up and over backward point. Very well played.
fires in a yorker, stabbed to the on side
length delivery on the off stump line, Dhoni drives on the up to long on
full and on the off stump, Dravid leans forward to get it to right of long on

full in length, outside off, Dravid goes for a slog-drive, makes contact with the inner-half of the bat but still gets it to the boundary at widish long on region. Flintoff tries to stop it with a sliding dive in to the advertising hoardings. Not a smart move, considering he has just come back from a injury
full in length, outside off. Wide called. A harsh call.
short of length, outside off, Dhoni gets on top of the bounce, punches it through backward point
full in length, just outside off, driven to long on
almost at the blockhole length, outside off, stabbed away down the track
full-toss, on the off stump line and Dhoni flat-bats it straight down the ground.
beautifully picked up. It was overpitched on the middle and leg, Dravid leant forward and whipped it over midwicket. Dravid reaches his fifty.
tries to correct his line but sends this one full and well outside off, Dravid leans across on a bent knee to square drive to boundary.
full and on the middle and leg, whipped to deep midwicket
fine-leg is in and Broad serves one full and on the legs, glanced away past that man
full and outside off, Dhoni shapes to square drive but lets it go through to Prior.
full toss, on the off stump line, swatted away to long on
full, right up there, at the bast of middle stump, stabbed away to the on side
full and on the legs, Dravid whips it to left of deep square leg where Tremlett dives but can't stop the ball. The outfield is pretty quick. That one just raced away
attempted yorker, on the off stump line, driven to left of long off
slower one, on the middle and off, Dravid taps it gently on the off side and picks up a single
at the blockhole, on the off and middle line, dug out to cover
fullish, on the off and middle, driven to extra cover
yorker, just outside off, stabbed away to cover for a single. 50 of the partnership comes up in 33 balls.
another yorker on the off stump line and Dhoni goes for his unique bottom-handed twirl over mid on and edges it to the on side
full pitched on the off stump line, pushed to cover
full toss outside leg, Dhoni tries to swat it away but can't reach and Prior dives to make a half-stop
another full toss, waist-high,  and Dravid spanks it over midwicket. Another gift-wrapped boundary.
backs away to the on side and slices a full-pitched delivery in the air towards deep point. Broad rushes in and dives in front and the ball just lands short of him. Brave decision to go for the catch

a slow bouncer does the trick. It was banged in short and it climbed up ever so slowly, Dhoni swivelled, was made to wait before he pulled it uppishly to the right of short-fine leg where Tremlett pulled off a sharp catch
yorker on the middle stump line, dabbed to square leg
full, straight, on the middle stump line, Karthik shapes to play it to the on side, gets a leading edge, past backward point
backed to the leg side, Flintoff hurled in a full toss on the middle stump line and Dravid slashed it past point
shuffles right across the sticks and flicks a full-pitched delivery outside off to midwicket
Karthik shuffles to the off side and tries to pull a short of length delivery on the leg side but doesn't connect. Wide called.
yorker gets Karthik. It was full, on the leg stump line and hit him low on the left leg. The hawk eye suggests it would have clipped the leg stump

full-pitched, outside off and Dravid gave himself room by backing away to the legside and carved it over point. The boundaries are quite short here and would you believe it, this one has screamed over the boundary.
full toss on the legs, pulled to deep midwicket
another full toss, just above waist-high, swatted away to deep midwicket. It was dipping. Dravid looks at the square-leg umpire, looking for a no-ball call but ..
low full toss on the off stump, Dravid backed away to the leg side and cut it late to third man boundary.
full and outside off, Dravid has a flash and a miss
Full and just outside off, Agarkar moves to the leg side, goes for a big drive through the off side and gets a thickish edge to Prior
full and on the legs, flicked away to fine leg for a single. Dravid comes back to strike
full and in the blockhole, dug out towards long off for a single. Good tight over this. Just two runs so far.
Flintoff gets a five-for. Quite similar to the Agarkar dismissal. Full, straight, just outside off, Powar tries to slog-drive it over cover but ends up edging it to Prior
full-toss on the off stump line, dabbed to point for a single
low full toss, at the base of middle stump, driven to right of long on.

inn2.comm: Full and swinging down the leg side.
Gets it right this time, just on the off stump line, guided to point
slips down the leg side again, wide called.
back to the off stump line, defended on the front foot. What next?
sticks to that off stump line, Cook leans forward to ease it to cover
on the leg and middle, clipped off the pads, past square leg. The outfield is pretty fast and the ball races away to the boundary
on the middle and leg, worked to midwicket
lands on a length, around middle and off, Cook gets on to the front foot to defend
fullish, lands outside leg stump, moves in and Prior is hit on the pad as he tries to flick it away
on the leg stump line, moving across Prior who tries to shape it to the on side, misses and it thuds into the inner thigh
fuller, just outside off, driven back to the bowler
on a length, slanting across Prior who jabs at it and gets a inside-edge to the on side
short of length, outside off stump, cut away to wide third man where Powar rushes across to his right and makes a diving stop. Dwayne Leverock would have approved.
full and on the off stump line, driven to cover
beaten. Full and outside off, Prior tries to drive on the up but ...
slips down the leg side and Prior clips it away past square leg.
lands on a length, on the off and middle, defended to the on side
fullish, on the legs, Cook wrists it away to deep square leg region where Munaf Patel makes quite a poor effort to stop it. He runs to his right and tries to stop it with his boot.
Poor delivery - full and outside off, slashed past point. 14 runs came in that over.
on the middle and leg, turned behind square leg for a single
whack. Half-volley outside off, Cook leans forward to cream it away through extra cover.
lands on a length, on the off stump line, moves in towards middle, worked to the on side. One slip is in place.
nice swinging delivery outside off, Cook has a stab and a miss.
lands short of length,on the middle line, Cook works it to square-leg. England need 303 from 46.1 overs
outswinger in the zone outside off, left alone

Dropped by Ganguly at first slip. Full and outside off, Prior has a flash and gets a thick outside edge. Dhoni moves to his right, but decides from going for the catch. Ganguly is a bit surprised and is late in putting his left hand out and ends up palming it away. It was Dhoni's catch.
way outside the off stump to interest Prior
full and outside off, Prior leans forward to play a cracking square drive. That went at some speed.
length delivery outside off, pushed to cover point
full in length, just outside off, steered to point
on the middle and leg, Cook plants his left foot across and gets his bat around the pad to play to the on side. This approach had him in trouble in the Tests
Full and down the leg side, another wide.
on the middle and leg, tucked to square leg and before Chawla can come into play, he will get a single
full and in the zone outside off stump, Cook covers the off stump and shoulders arms
lands on a length, just outside off stump and curves away. Cook is beaten by the movement ; his feet went nowhere while his bat chased the ball
lands outside off, on a length and curved away, left alone
on the off stump line, slightly short of a length, Cook stayed adjacent to the line and punched it past the diving Yuvrak at point.
fuller, on a good length, just outside off stump and Cook lets that one go through to Dhoni
beaten by the outswinger. Prior is almost lured into a fatal prod
fullish, curving away from Prior who leans forward to drive through cover. Crisply driven.
Cracking stroke. Short of length, just outside off and Prior punches it on the up, through covers.
fuller, on the middle and off, Prior shapes to drive straight but is beaten by the late outswing and gets a leading edge to point
Here comes the wide. Down the leg side. England off to a flier.
short of length, on the off stump line, Prior punches on the up and Karthik makes a half-stop at short cover
lands on a length, on the off stump, pushed to mid off
full and outside off, guided to wide third man
on the middle and leg, clipped past square leg and Chawla tries gamely but can't prevent the boundary
on the middle and off, nagging line and length, defended back to the bowler
on the off stump line, on a good length, driven to mid off
in the zone outside off, left alone
fullish and on the legs, chipped over square leg for a boundary. The run-fest continues.
short of length, on the legs, glanced to fine leg
short of length, on the middle and leg, defended to the on side
on the off stump line, pushed to cover
on the length, around the off stump line, punched to cover

kicks up from short of length after landing on the middle stump line, curved in a touch and thuds in to the left thigh and bobs away to Ganguly at first slip, Ganguly appeals for a catch. Nice try Sourav.
Another one that rears up from short of length, Cook shapes to pull but is beaten by the pace. The ball rammed into the midriff and popped up in the air and fell dangerously close to the stumps
short of length, on the middle and leg, glanced to backward square-leg for a single
on the off stump line, pushed to point
just over square leg. RP Singh banged it in short, Cook goes for a pull, makes contact with the top half of the bat and it just bobs over Chawla at square leg
slap. Short of length and outside off, Cook spanked it past point.
fuller, straighter, Cook is into his drive a touch early and it almost carries to the bowler.
nice curving delivery around the off stump and Prior is beaten on the drive
hits the deck short of length, around the off stump, pushed to cover
again pings the short of length, just outside off stump, punched to point
Caught by Ganguly at midwicket but hold on ... it's a no-ball. Munaf again goes for the back of length and Prior pulls it limply to Ganguly but ...
another one that climbs up short of length, outside off stump, guided to point.

Munaf gets his man.  Another one that kicks up from short of length, Prior makes room by moving to the leg side and tries to flat-bat it but ends up skying it high towards mid off. Dravid comes under it and had to wait for a while before gravity took charge and took a well-judged catch. Munaf has been impressive and has broken through for India.
Munaf strikes again. Two in two. It landed on a good length, around the off stump and slanted away, Cook has a tentative poke and that proves fatal. Gone.
on the middle and leg, from a length, tucked away to square leg
short of length, angling across Bell who places it to left of point
bangs it in short and outside off stump, Pietersen sways away
another short ball but this one slips down the leg side. Doctrove extends his arms.
full and swinging in, on the leg and middle, Pietersen tries to flick it away, misses and is struck on the pad. RP Singh appeals for a lbw decision but it was going down leg side.
on the middle and leg, tapped in front of square leg, Chawla swoops in, has a shy at the striker's end, misses and Bell makes it. It might have got interesting had it hit the sticks.
Dropped by Powar at third man. Short and outside off,  Bell can't keep the upper-cut down and it flies to right of Powar who makes a mess of a relatively simple chance.
Wide outside the off stump gives him another crack at the hattrick
on a length, well outside off stump and Bell has a flash and a miss.
on the off stump line, defended to cover
on the off stump line, guided to point
kicks up short of length, outside off stump, Bell has a nervous dab at it and gets a inside-edge to fine leg
nice nagging delivery on the off stump. It was full in length and cut away late, Bell pushed at it tentatively and gets a thickish outside edge to third man
full in length, slanting away from Bell who square drives to point
Homing in on the off stump and Bell pushes it back down the track.
lands on a length, outside off, shapes in towards off and Bell is on the back foot, pushing it to the off side
again homes in on the off stump, nice curve in, Bell gets right behind the line to defend
on the off and middle stump line, and Bell lets it come to him before tucking it behind square-leg for a single
banged in short, still from round the stumps, Pietersen stays back, gets on to his toes to get on top of the bounce, fends it away behind square-leg and gets two runs.
in that temptation zone outside off, left alone by Bell
fuller, closer to the off stump, Bell shoulders arms again. Good tight spell from Munaf.
133.kph, on the off stump line, curving away from Bell who lets that one to go through to Dhoni
banged in short, on the leg and middle, Bell swivels quickly to pull it past square-leg
short of length, on the off stump line, pushed to the off side.
slightly short of length, outside off stump and Bell punches it on the up through cover point. Fab stroke.
lands on a length, outside off stump and moves away. Bell is not interested, Munaf stares at Bell who puts his head down and quickly walks across to have a chat with Pietersen.
full and outside off stump, driven uppishly to left of short cover.
100 is up with a upper-cut. short and outside off, cut over backward point.
full and outside off, left alone
short of length, on the off stump line, punched to cover
fuller, on the off and middle, angling in to Bell who drives to mid off
lands on a length, on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
short of length, outside off stump, punched to cover
full and on the middle and leg, Pietersen gets behind the line to wrist it past square leg.
full in length, on the middle and leg, Pietersen gets behind the line to clip it through midwicket. Nice forcing stroke off the back foot.
lands on a length, on the middle, Pietersen works his bottom-hand over time to wrist it away to long leg
bangs it in short but the line goes awry. It flies way outside off stump and Dhoni dives to his right, gets a glove but can't hold on to it.
fuller, straighter, on the middle, worked to square leg
lands on a length, on the off stump, cuts away from Bell who opens the bat-face to guide to left of Yuvraj Singh at point.
full and outside off, square-driven to point
on the middle, full and straight, driven to mid-on
swing and a miss. Short of length and outside off, Bell goes for a cut but ...
short of length, homing in on the middle, pushed back to the bowler
Agarkar completes a maiden over. Full and outside off, Bell square drives to point where Yuvraj makes the stop and throws down the stumps at the non-striker's end but Pietersen is home.
on a length, around the off and middle, Pietersen stays back to punch it to mid on

Dropped by Dhoni.  It landed on a length, just outside off and cut away a touch. Pietersen tried to play a cute late cut and it ran off the face of the bat but Dhoni couldn't hold on. Ganguly screams in agony.
on the middle and leg, whipped to midwicket

Dropped by Ganguly. Short of length, just outside off stump, Pietersen tries to punch it off the back foot, is a touch early into his stroke and ends up pushing it in the air, low to the left of Ganguly who gets both hands to it but fails to cling on. Pietersen survives again.
short of length, on the off stump line, punched to cover
bangs it in short, just outside off and Pietersen pulls it in front of square. Imperious stroke.
Ah! he just walks across to a full-pitched delivery just outside off stump and whips it through midwicket. Pietersen plays that shot pretty well.
full and outside off stump, Pietersen slashes it past a diving Yuvraj Singh and Powar comes across from third man to make the stop
full and straight, on the middle and off, driven to mid-on
on the off stump line, on a good length, pushed to extra cover
full in length, just outside off stump, Pietersen shapes to off drive but gets a inner edge and the ball rolls to right of mid on
full and outside off, cut to right of Agarkar at third man
lands on a length, outside off stump, driven to cover
on the off stump line, on a length, driven to cover again
bit of width offered outside off and Pietersen drills it to sweeper cover
Full and on the off stump line, Bell leans forward to ease it between the bowler and the mid-off fielder. England continue to attack.
quickish topspinner, on the off stump, punched to mid off

Piyush Chawla cleans up Pietersen with a one that didn't spin much. Pietersen can't believe it. It landed on the middle and off and went on almost straight. Pietersen anticipated a bit more turn and got his bat down in an angle, outside the line of the delivery. The ball threaded the bat and pad gap, slid in, brushed the inner half of the front pad and crashed into the off stump. Chawla is over the moon, Pietersen looks dazed.
landed outside off stump, on a length, pushed to the off side
on the middle and leg, worked to wide midwicket for a single
googly on the middle line, pushed back to the bowler
full and outside off, square-driven to right of deep point
full and outside off stump, left alone
this one comes in after landing on a length outside off, defended on the front foot
floats it full and straight on the middle and off, driven to long off
slightly short of length, on the middle and leg and it sits up nicely for Colling wood to pull it away in front of square
drifting on to the pads, clipped to left of long leg for two runs
a touch short of length, outside off stump, Bell goes back to punch it to cover where Karthik misfields
on the middle line, defended on the front foot
comes down the track, reaches the pitch of the delivery and drives to mid off
tossed-up, outside off and Collingwood goes down on his knee to play the slog-sweep.
on the mdidle and leg, slight turn, drives to long on
gets some sharp turn straightaway. It landed outside off stump and broke in sharply, right across Collingwood. Dhoni gathered it down the leg side
bit more flight, full and outside off, Collingwood leans forward to drive it through extra cover
lands outside off, spins in , defended on the front foot
comes down the track, reaches the pitch to drive to long off

again sharp bit of turn. It landed outside off and ripped across Bell, again Dhoni gathers down the leg side. The camera pans to the umpire who just shakes his head. He must have thought about signalling it a wide.
turns in from outside off, glanced to backward square-leg
beaten full and just outside off stump and Bell is beaten, trying to cut. Too full for that shot.
lands on the leg stump line, turns in a touch and Bell is struck on the pad, trying to play a flick shot
a tad wide outside off stump, cut away to deep point
from wide of the crease, a googly, cut away to backward point where Yuvraj makes a diving stop
spins in from outside off, defended down the track
goes back, waits for the spin to play out before tucking it behind square leg for a single

Unlike Bell, Collingwood likes to come down the track and he does so again this time. He reaches the pitch, drives to left of midwickety where Rohit Sharma, substitute for Tendulkar, stops and has a direct hit at the non-striker's end. He gives away an extra run in the process
on the middle and leg, Bell stays back to wrist it behind square leg
flighted delivery outside off, driven to long off
on the middle and leg, turning in, worked to short fine leg
on the middle and leg, dabbed to the on side
fuller, on the middle, driven to long on
slider on the middle and off, Bell backs away to the leg side to cut to deep point.
dipping full toss, on the middle and leg, driven to long on
short in length, on the middle and leg, Bell threatens to go forward before pushing back to pull it through midwicket
beaten It lands on a length, around the off and middle, Bell tries to step down the track sees the length, goes back to cut and is beaten.
full and just outside off, steered to backward point
flighted delivery outside off, Collingwood waltzes down the track to play a nice chip stroke over midwicket.
beaten in the flight this time. Again, Collingwood comes down the track, the ball dips rapidly and turns in to beat the intended chip-stroke and hits the pad
quicker one, straighter too , just outside off, and Collingwood is beaten as he plays inside the line. Good over this.
on the off and middle, slightly short, pushed to point

Googly does the trick. Collingwood skips down the track and plays all around a googly that landed on the off and middle line. The ball breaks in to brush the inner half of the front pad before going on to hit the stumps. Good spin bowling from both ends has led to this dismissal.
Hello?! Flintoff decides to announce himself with a cracking cover drive. Admittedly it was  overpitched, but still had to be put away.
spins away from Flintoff who pushes to cover region for a single
turns away from Bell who shoulders arms
lands on the off stump and slides in much to the chagrin of Bell who somehow manages to jab it away at the last minute.
too short and Flintoff has no problem in pulling it to deep square-leg boundary
better stuff from Powar. Loopy delivery that spun in from outside off, Flintfoff lunges at it, gets a inside-edge on to the pad and it bobs away to vacant short-leg region
nicely flighted delivery that turns in, Flintoff is beaten in the air and is struck on the pad. The point of impact was just outside off stump, though.

Powar entices Flintoff to his doom. Loopy flighted delivery on the off stump and Flintoff shapes for a huge lofted shot. But the ball dips rapidly on him and his attemped heave goes straight to Agarkar at deep midwicket
spins in from outside off, worked to midwicket
flat delivery on the middle and leg, worked to midwicket
turns away from Bell who runs it to backward point region
flighted delivery on the middle and leg , worked past midwicket
flighted stuff, outside off stump and Bell leans forward to cream it through cover
spins in from outside off, defended on the front foot
spins down the leg side, Dhoni gathers and goes up in appeal. It doesn't work. Wide is called.
spins in from outside off, glanced to short backward fine leg
tossed up on the middle and off, worked to midwicket
short of length, on the pads, tucked behind square leg for a single
leans forward, gets to the pitch and drives to long on
on the middle and off, dabbed to short cover region for a single
on the middle and leg, slightly short in length, clipped past midwicket
comes down the track and swings a fullish delivery to deep midwicket. He reaches his 12th ODI fifty with that stroke.
from round the stumps, on the middle stump line, full, Bell tries to dab it to the off side, gets a inside-edge to the on side
full and on the middle and leg, Bell gets a leading edge to mid off, trying to play across the line to the on side
on the leg and middle line and Bell pulls out a reverse sweep, more a reverse paddle, and the ball rolls to short third man.
spins in from outside off, worked to right of Karthik at midwicket
lands outside off, on a length, turns in, Bell goes back and across, waits for the turn before tucking it past square leg
flighted it above the eye-level, outside off, driven to Rohit Sharma at long on
flatter on the leg and middle line, Bell tries to flick, misses and it runs to right of short-fine leg fielder
slower through the air, on the middle stump line, turned to square leg
goes back to wrist a delivery spinning in from off stump, past square leg for a single
flights it across, full and on the middle, driven to long on
goes round the stumps for Bell. It lands outside leg stump and strikes him on the pad
full and outside leg, swept to long leg
stays round the stumps for Bopara too. Googly down the leg side. Wide called
lands on the leg stump line, turns in, defended on the front foot
lands full and outside leg, swept to long leg
lands on a length, on the middle, holds its line, cut to deep point
short of length, just outside off, punched to long on
well flighted delivery outside off stump, driven to cover
slows up the pace this time, Bopara is made to wait and he pushes it limply to midwicket

flighted delivery on the middle line and Bopara goes for a sweep, ends up top-edging it towards long leg where it falls well short of Munaf. The ball spins away from Munaf who gets in a bit of tangle trying to stop that
on the off stump line, driven back to Powar who flicks a throw between his legs at the non-striker's end. Hmm...
full in length, on the off stump line, driven to cover
full, middle and leg, wristed past midwicket
fullish, on the leg and middle, Bopara whips it away through midwicket region and RP Singh runs across from deep square leg but is too slow for the ball
Munaf traps Bopara. Dead plumb. Full in length, on the middle stump line, Bopara, again, tries to whip it across the line but ends up playing all around it and is struck in front.
full-pitched on the legs, flicked to left of RP Singh at deep square leg
slightly short in length, outside off stump, not much turn in, Bell goes right back to work it to midwicket region
slows up the pace, gets it to turn in from outside off, Mascarenhas shuffles across and tries to work it to the on side, misses but is struck just outside off stump
flighted delivery outside off, driven to long off

huge appeal for lbw. It landed on a length, on the middle stump line, turned in a touch and Bell was hit on the pad as he shuffled across. The leg stump was visible when he was hit on the pad and I think the ball would have clipped the leg stump.
tries a reverse sweep but can't beat the short third man fielder
kicks up from short of length, just outside off stump and Mascarenhas is surprised at the extra bounce,  has a poke and is beaten
full in length, outside off, stabbed away close on the off side and will get a single
Full-pitched outside off stump, Mascarenhas frees his arms and slashes it to right of deep cover where Powar moves smartly and makes a diving stop. Dravid looks pretty pleased with the effort,
full and on the middle stump, defended to the off side for a quick single
floated on the middle and leg, lapped around the corner
rips it full and on the middle and leg, Bell was looking to come down the track  but is beaten by the full length and is struck on the pad
gets a single with a drive through midwicket
flatter, quicker, straighter, on the middle, dabbed to midwicket
full, almost yorker-length, on the middle line, driven to long on
full and outside off, whipped to deep midwicket
comes down the track, reaches the pitch of the delivery and sends it soaring over long off

goes round the stumps and gets his man. Bell charges down the track again, backing to the legside in the process, but is bit cramped up by the line - outside leg- and lofts straight to Munaf Patel at long on
flatter and outside off, Broad tries to paddle it away and is hit on the pad
Broad is beaten by the googly
on the middle stump line, swept to long leg
spins in from outside leg stump, loopy delivery and Broad is beaten in the air and then by the turn.
quicker and flatter, on the off and middle, punched to cover
slows up the pace, tosses it outside leg stump, Broad is made to wait and on drives it past midwicket
flatter and that one with the arm. Straight outside off stump and he is beaten completely
Mascarenhas responds with a slog-sweep. Up and over deep midwicket.
fuller, on the middle, dabbed to backward square leg
comes down the track and is beaten by the on that landed on the leg stump line, and slid down the leg side. The ball runs off the pad to fine leg
Another slog-sweep. Another six. He went down on his knee to dispose that.
Chawla goes round the stumps. On the leg stump line, lapped around the corner

Another mighty blow. Mascarenhas gets the crowd going. It landed outside leg stump and he biffed it over long leg. He is enjoying himself out there. So far has displayed only one productive stroke - that slog sweep - but eh ... he is cashing in on that.
full and on the middle line, nudged to the off side for a single
full in length, on the leg stump line, pushed past RP Singh, down to long on
length delivery on the off and middle, Broad square drives on the up and gets it past point
full and on the middle and off, driven to cover
banged in short, just outside off stump, Broad tries to cut it but is beaten by the bounce.
on a length, just outside off, Broad slashes it to left of Agarkar at third man
full and slower one, on the middle, driven past square-leg
delivered with the round-arm action, full and outside off, Mascarenhas backs away to the leg side and couldn't reach the delivery as a result
bangs this one short and outside off, Mascarenhas lets that one go past him, may be he thought that would be called a wide but ...
fuller, outside off and carved to right of wide third man where RP Singh makes a mess of it and gives away an extra run
full in length, outside off, pushed to point where Uthappa hurls in a quick throw to Agarkar
driven to wide long off where Rohit Sharma fields and hurls in a throw at the striker's end. Agarkar, at the non-striker's end, is not too happy, "Idhar yaar," he screams. (Over here)
full in length, on the stumps, Broad backs away to the leg side, tries to drive and ends up inside-edging it, along the ground, to the 'keeper
swing and a miss. Fullish, just outside off stump and Broad tries to heave it out of the ground but doesn't connect
lands on a length, outside off, punched past point
Ah! not the slog-sweep this time. He takes the left leg out of the line and drills a full delivery over long off.
banged in short and pulled in the air but well short of deep midwicket
another short delivery, Broad goes for a pull shot but no leather on wood.
full and outside off, again delivered with a round-arm action, and the almost yorker-length beats the intended heave

That's six no. 5 and it lands on the roof at wide long on. That was some hit. It was a slower delivery but Mascarenhas picked it up early, waited before smoking it high over the boundary ropes. That one kept travelling.
slings across a low full toss, on the off stump, carted away to long off
on the length, on the middle and leg, Broad tries to flick it , misses but will get a leg bye. It brings the marauder on striker
serves up a bouncer and Mascarenhas can't connect with his pull shot.

Another short-pitched stuff, outside the off stump and Mascarenhas doesn't connect again but they rush across for a single. Dhoni had gathered it but they still get across in time. Broad had rushed out as soon as Agarkar had delivered.

backs to the leg side, RP Singh follows him with a short of length delivery but Mascarenhas twists his body and manages to short-arm jab it to square leg boundary. That's fifty for Mascarenhas. It has been pretty entertaining.
lands on a length, outside off, tries to flat-bat it and gets a inner edge, along the ground,  to the 'keeper
low full toss, swatted past midwicket. The ball made contact with the bottom-half of the bat and hence doesn't travel far
bouncer that sails harmlessly down the leg side. Dhoni does well to gather it
Mascarenhas's breezy cameo ends. Death by aggression. He tries to pull a short-of-length delivery over midwicket but ends up lobbing it to midwicket. And then they were two.
fuller, on the middle and leg, driven to long on
backs to the leg side, RP follows him and Tremlett is hit on the thigh pad as he tries to unsuccessfully pull.
Short of length, on the leg stump and Broad tonks it over deep midwicket. Powar runs back, catches it and tries to flick it back in but he has already gone beyond the ropes. The crowd love it.
Ah! The lemon cut. It was full in length, outside off, Broad tries to drill it through cover, gets a inside-edge and it runs to fine leg boundary.
shuffles right across the stumps, attempts a big heave across the line but can't connect
20 from 3 and what does Broad do. Smokes a full toss on the off stump over long off. The crowd roar their approval
Another lemon cut. Another boundary. England now need 10 to win from one ball. Will Munaf bowl a no ball?
India have won. It was full and outside off, Broad shuffled across and attempts another heave but doesn't connect.
